Description: Reads and writes Cloud Optimized Point Cloud (COPC, .copc.laz)
    files from local disk or HTTP(S) endpoints using range reads. Returns
    point data as 'data.table' with 'rlas'-compatible header conventions.
    Optionally converts to 'lidR' LAS objects when 'lidR' is installed.
    Uses 'LASzip' for LAZ decompression. Supports spatial bounding box,
    polygon area-of-interest (AOI), corridor, Z-range, and attribute
    filters via the COPC octree hierarchy. Provides multi-resolution
    level-of-detail (LOD) sampling, deterministic tiling, streaming
    iterators, 'lidR' catalog integration, and STAC endpoint discovery
    (including the USGS 3DEP collection via Microsoft Planetary Computer).
